      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of relief might sound appealing, but it's a coping mechanism that doesn't mean you've failed as a parent. It's a sign that you're carrying the weight of their well-being on your own shoulders, and that's not sustainable. Remember that your presence may bring stress, but it also brings stability and a sense of security that they need. Try to separate your self-worth from their lives and acknowledge that being present isn't a burden, it's a choice.",
      "source": "target",
